Arrays : Arrays are used to store multiple values in a single variable, instead of declaring separate variables for each value.

To declare an array, define the variable type with square brackets [ ] :

String[] cars; // datatype [] array_name

example: To create an array of integers, you could write:
         int[] myNum = {10, 20, 30, 40};

Access the Elements of an Array : 
You can access an array element by referring to the index number.

This statement accesses the value of the first element in cars:

Example:
String[] cars = {"Volvo", "BMW", "Ford", "Mazda"};
System.out.println(cars[0]);
// Outputs : Volvo

Properties of Array :
Array Length : To find out how many elements an array has, use the length property:
Example :
String[] cars = {"Volvo", "BMW", "Ford", "Mazda"};
